   <topic>*TO_HEX Function</topic>
      <description>Convert binary data to hexadecimal data.</description>
      
   <syntax>Value as N = *TO_HEX(B data)</syntax>
   <arguments>
     <argument>
         <name>data</name>
         <description>An integer value to be converted to hexadecimal format.</description>
     </argument>
   </arguments>

   <discussion>
The *TO_HEX() function converts a number to an hexadecimal string.
   </discussion>
   <example><![CDATA[
? *to_hex(123)
= "0000007B"
]]></example>
  
